Health Minister Dr Zweli Mkhize briefs the community of Pietermaritzburg. Courtesy #DStv403 PIETERMARITZBURG - Health Minister Dr Zweli Mkhize says South Africans shouldn't fear the Coronavirus, they should rather understand how to defeat it. Mkhize was briefing the community of Pietermaritzburg. READ: SA confirms third coronavirus case That's after a third person tested positive for COVID-19. The third patient is the wife of the first man diagnosed with the virus. READ: What you need to know about coronavirus The minister says it was always only a matter of time before South Africa confirmed its first coronavirus case. On Thursday, South Africa reported its first case of coronavirus. A 38-year-old man tested positive for the COVID-19 virus in KwaZulu-Natal. The man recently travelled to Italy.